reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars They take a beating!
reviews.reviewText: When I first bought the nesting luggage I wasn't happy on how thin the luggage was and thought it would not last long - surprise! It's tough and holds much more than my old soft luggage. They went on two cruises and came back in the same shape that they left in. Easy to store because they nest - I put by backpacks in the smaller case then nest the rest. They hold more because they break in half and have a net to hold the top in when you close them. Easy to use and roll quite easily. Haven't figured out the locks yet but that's not why I bought them. I am moving to a condo and dont need different suitcases hanging around (they fit in our cabin closet easily). Am very satisfied with this set.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The quality of plastic is very reliable
reviews.reviewText: Irreplaceable suitcases, for all occasions . If you fly somewhere for a short time, the smallest suitcase is suitable, its size is suitable for hand luggage. If we fly for a week with the family, we take all three. The quality of plastic is very reliable and withstands even extreme conditions in the luggage compartment of the airplane.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars UPDATE! Wheel broke
reviews.reviewText: UPDATE-- The company reached out to me and offered a full refund. I took it. Because of the generous refund, I am changing from 2 to 4 stars.I ordered this set many months before a long trip. The wheel on the biggest suitcase broke off when we got to the airport to come home. It was glitching/catching before that. For two of the three weeks, we were on a cruise and the suitcase was empty under the bed. It was not a strenuous trip. None of the wheels on the other suitcases broke or wobbled. That's why I'm giving two stars. I will update my review when I hear back from the company.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 14, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I'm loving this neon green color. It's lightweight and the wheels glid smoothly. The zippers are good quality. I thought I was going to receive something cheap looking but to my surprise these bags look and feel the same as any other expensive luggage.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I would recommend
reviews.reviewText: We purchased these for our cruise trip. They held up being tossed around at the airport and baggage collection at the cruise port. The wheels roll with ease and there's plenty of room. Very pleased with this set of luggage.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Highly recommend! EASY to move, 360 degree turning radius, surprisingly LIGHT & durable!
reviews.reviewText: When I first received this, I was concerned it wouldn't be robust enough to put up with the rigors of travel - especially being tossed into the luggage bay of an airplane - it's SO LIGHT WEIGHT!On my last flight, my old trusty wheeled bag was fatally wounded with one end being ripped up irreparably. So I (reluctantly) replaced it by picking up this trusty case, as I had another trip coming up soon - My old bag had a very heavy, cumbersome "frame" into which the extendable handle would nestle, and I loved that bag, but I had NO idea how much I was missing.I also have chronic joint pain issues, which makes travel very painful, especially if I have myriad items hanging over my back/shoulders through many hours of travel, and having to rush through an airport to make my connecting flight - the whole ordeal makes it increasingly important that I plan ahead for exactly how much I'm going to have to carry vs. "drag" around with me, etc.I really was awed by how lightweight and EASY TO MOVE this case was. It's quite a bit smaller in overall dimensions than my "old trusty" bag was, but I was amazed how roomy this was inside - I was able to pack just as much as in my nearly twice-the-size previous go-to, and the 360 degree casters made this SO MUCH EASIER to maneuver.And because the case itself was so lightweight, I was able to pack it to the hilt and STILL stay WAY under the weight limits for this size bag at the airline.But the real test came when I took the trip itself, and the bag went through all the trauma of being tossed and banged around, and there were no cracks, it proved durable to the task, and I couldn't be more pleased!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Quality issues but seller made it right
reviews.reviewText: Update: After posting my initial review the seller immediately reached out to offer a full refund and made things right.Original: Excited by the bright yellow color. So based on a a wheel breaking off not even through the first trip I would not recommend these suitcases due to lack of quality.
